Class TimeTracker

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dv8tion.jda.core.hooks.ListenerAdapter
      • TimeTracker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.dv8tion.jda.core.hooks.EventListener

    public class TimeTracker
extends net.dv8tion.jda.core.hooks.ListenerAdapter
    A Discord bot that tracks and logs user messages if they contain clock in/out key words; it then calculates the time differences between those messages, and finally sends the command user the list of messages that contained the clock in/out key words and their calculated times.

      • onGuildMessageReceived

        public void onGuildMessageReceived(net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.message.guild.GuildMessageReceivedEvent event)
        Handles the command input via a guild TextChannel that the bot is a part of. Commands:
        /times MM/dd/yy (Gets clock ins/outs and the total hours for each member. Admin use only.)
        /clocks @User MM/dd/yy (Gets the clock ins/outs for the specified User. Open use.)
        Overrides:
        onGuildMessageReceived in class net.dv8tion.jda.core.hooks.ListenerAdapter
        Parameters:
        event - Event that holds the User, TextChannel, and command info.

      • getTimes

        private void getTimes(net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.User cmdUser,
                      net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.TextChannel channel,
                      java.lang.String dateAsString)
        Method that is called when the command '/times MM/dd/yy' is used. Gets the TextChannel's members and their messages from the channel the command was entered from and adds them to tracker. Also produces the twoWeekStartDate and twoWeekEndDate from the 'MM/dd/yy' parameter. Finally, it calls sendMemberInfo(User, TextChannel, Member, List) to send the user of the command the requested info.
        Parameters:
        cmdUser - The User that entered the command.
        channel - The TextChannel from which the messages are being pulled from.
        dateAsString - The 'MM/dd/yy' parameter given from the '/times MM/dd/yy' command.

      • getClocks

                       net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.TextChannel channel,
                       net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.User user,
                       java.lang.String dateAsString)
        Method that is called when the command '/clocks @User MM/dd/yy' is used. Gets the User's Message}s up to two weeks from the entered date. Messages are then sent to the command user.
        Parameters:
        cmdUser - The User that entered the command.
        channel - The TextChannel from which the messages are being pulled from.
        user - The User who's messages are being pulled.
        dateAsString - The 'MM/dd/yy' parameter given from the '/clocks @User MM/dd/yy' command.

      • getTimeDifferences

        private double getTimeDifferences(java.util.List<net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Message> clocks)

Also adds single clocks to singleClocks (a clock-in missing a clock-out) for future logging with logSinglesToFile(Member).

        Returns:
